You&#39;re right... so I&#39;ve added your accomplishments as a note under 
that blog history entry you saw. Right under the 24 Nov 2007 date 
event.

http://ufomagazine.blogspot.com/2008/10/move-over-franks-box-radio-
shack-hack.html

By-the-way:
I&#39;ve got the new version of the 12-470 (black case) torn apart on my 
bench again.  I know I failed to get it hacked the first time (last 
year), but I figured I&#39;d try it again.  It is totally different than 
the others... and they have made sure you can&#39;t tell what the radio 
chip is by getting rid of the markings and covering both sides of the 
circuit board with a waxy substance. I&#39;ve been carefully scraping it 
away. The chip is a 30 pin device, possibly a KK22425 or KK22426 or 
equivilent.
The mute pin for the #25 is pin 2 but looking at the connection 
scheme itmight not be the right one.
I guess I&#39;ll mess with it until I break it... or ???

I&#39;ll put some pictures of the new 12-470 circuit board in my photo 
area of this froum.

- Mike

